            <title>[PIG-3936] DBStorage fails on storing nulls for non varchar columns</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3936</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When trying to store a null value into an integer column in Postgres we were getting a JDBC error on the insert statement.  I tracked it down to always using varchar as the type when writing nulls in Pig.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix the issue I use the schema (if present) to determine the type of the field with the null value.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
